.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-12::.
There 4 different types of food: corn, lime, onion, pineapple
The people use 4 different means of transport: boat, bike, tram, car
1. the person eating onion is not to the right of the person driving the car##8
2. the person driving the boat is not to the right of the person eating lime##8
3. the person driving the bike is somewhere to the right of the person eating pineapple##5
4. the person driving the boat is on the far left or far right##3
5. the person eating onion is between the person driving the car and the person driving the tram##2
6. the person eating lime is on the far left##1
7. the person eating onion is on the left or right of the person driving the car##3

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1      |     2     |     3      |    4    |
| Food    | lime        | pineapple | onion      | corn    |
| Transport   | boat | tram   | bike | car |

